[0;34mNext Steps[0m
[0;34m========================================[0m
[0;34m1. Configure your WAN:[0m
   Edit /etc/wanctl/spectrum.yaml on cake-shaper
   - Set router host, user
   - Set queue names to match your RouterOS config
   - Adjust bandwidth floors and ceilings

[0;34m2. Set up router credentials:[0m

   Option A - REST API (recommended for faster response):
     ssh cake-shaper 'sudo nano /etc/wanctl/secrets'
     Add: ROUTER_PASSWORD=your_router_password
     Set transport: "rest" in your config file

   Option B - SSH key authentication:
     Copy your router SSH key to /etc/wanctl/ssh/router.key
     sudo chown wanctl:wanctl /etc/wanctl/ssh/router.key
     sudo chmod 600 /etc/wanctl/ssh/router.key
     Set transport: "ssh" in your config file

[0;34m3. Migrate storage if this host has not already moved to the per-WAN DB layout:[0m
   Check for the archive marker first:
   ssh cake-shaper 'sudo test -f /var/lib/wanctl/metrics.db.pre-v135-archive && echo migrated || echo needs-migration'

   If the archive marker is missing, run from your workstation before restart/canary:
   ./scripts/migrate-storage.sh --ssh cake-shaper

[0;34m4. Restart the service:[0m
   ssh cake-shaper 'sudo systemctl enable --now wanctl@spectrum.service'

[0;34m5. Run post-restart canary:[0m
   ./scripts/canary-check.sh --ssh cake-shaper

   The canary validates health, storage, and latency signals after restart.
   Exit 0 = PASS, 1 = FAIL, 2 = WARN
   For threshold details or escalation steps, see: docs/RUNBOOK.md
[0;34m6. Monitor:[0m
   ssh cake-shaper 'sudo journalctl -u wanctl@spectrum.service -f'
   ssh cake-shaper 'sudo tail -f /var/log/wanctl/spectrum.log'
   ssh cake-shaper 'sudo systemctl status wanctl@spectrum.service'

[0;34m7. Capture operator summary and soak evidence:[0m
   ssh cake-shaper 'wanctl-operator-summary http://<health-ip-1>:9101/health http://<health-ip-2>:9101/health'
   ./scripts/soak-monitor.sh

[0;34m9. Collect profiling data (Phase 1):[0m
   After deployment, let the daemon run for 7-14 days
   Then extract profiling statistics:
   ssh cake-shaper 'python3 /opt/scripts/profiling_collector.py /var/log/wanctl/spectrum.log --all'

   Generate analysis report:
   ssh cake-shaper 'python3 /opt/scripts/analyze_profiling.py --log-file /var/log/wanctl/spectrum.log'

   See /opt/docs/PROFILING.md for detailed procedure

